The paper is about the special issue of the Journal of Theory and Practice of Logic Programming (TPLP) dedicated to the full papers accepted for the 28th International Conference on Logic Programming (ICLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages) which includes topics related to logic programming. The paper also mentions discussing work in the area of logic programming, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a relevant category. Additionally, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper discusses logic programming. cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are less likely categories, but they could be relevant if the paper discusses database or software engineering aspects of logic programming.
